Hawai'i Style Beef Stew
  --Catherine Toth Fox

1/3 c ap flour
1 1/2 tsp kosher salt, plus more as needed
1 tsp sugar
1/2 tsp freshly ground black pepper, plus more for serving
2 lb boneless beef chuck roast or beef stew meat, trimmed of surface fat and cut into 1 to 1 1/2" pieces
1 medium yellow onion, diced (~1 1/2 c)
3 medium carrots, peeled and cut crosswise into 1" thick rounds (~2 c)
2 medium stalks celery, cut crosswise into 1/2" thick pieces (~3/4 c)
1 pound gold potatoes (about 3 medium), cut into 1-inch pieces (~3 c)
14.5 oz can beef broth (scant 2 c)
8 oz can tomato sauce
2 tbsp Worcestershire sauce
shoyu or tamari (optional)
steamed white rice, for serving (optional)

Stir flour, salt, sugar, and black pepper together in a 6 qt or larger slow cooker. Add beef pieces and toss until evenly coated. Stir in onion, carrots, celery, and potatoes. Whisk broth, tomato sauce, and Worcestershire sauce together in a liquid measuring cup or medium bowl. Pour over the beef and vegetables and stir to combine. Cover and cook until the beef is very tender, 7-8 hr on the LOW setting or 4 hr on the HIGH setting. Taste and season with shoyu and more kosher salt or black pepper as needed. Serve with white rice if desired.



